snippet.textDisplay: I just left the grocery story and it was comical and pathetic at the same time..I was one of 4 people on the paper isle. Two guys passed by me and some lady who  was looking at ziplock bags. One of the two guys started to cough a lot. Luckily we were both further down the isle when it occured but that lady started screaming at the guy saying "No !No! Why would you come to the store without a mask" It's just not plain right" The two guys left right away and I was left there standing as she glared at me for approval. I did agree as I kindly motioned for her to move far back away from the aisle so that I could  grab my own ziplock bag selection. It was obvious that I was looking to keep my distance even from her,the grocery employees were discussing hand sanitizers and some guy in the register line before me was sniffling like he had a bad cold and the people parted like the red sea! You really had to be there to enjoy this comedy.

snippet.textDisplay: Not related to this bit at all, but the fundraiser. If your county isn't still providing food for needy students, especially during the pandemic, then you have a super shitty county. My county is providing bagged breakfast, lunch, and dinner, M-F, to any child in the county that is between 2 and 18 years old, regardless of their financial situation. They just have to drive or walk to the school to pick it up. "But we don't have the funding for that!" Bullshit. the schools already have food in the cafeteria kitchens that was to be used for school lunches. Food that needs to be cooked and eaten or it'll go bad. So if your county isn't handing out this food AT LEAST to needy students, they're just letting the food sit and rot. You need to vote that school board out because they suck ass at their jobs.
